cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IR. 

The paper discusses a scalable probabilistic graphical model for mining and discovering data insights, which is a common topic in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with big data problems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) as well. The use of probabilistic-based solutions and the application of the proposed model to solve two different challenging probabilistic-based problems suggest that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with hierarchical data, which could suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the application of the proposed model to solve a problem related to latent semantic discovery over search logs suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
